		"description": "<p>Every fey being loves a good riddle. You may use your action to pose a riddle to one creature you can see within 30 feet. The creature must be able to understand you. That creature must then succeed on a Wisdom saving throw versus your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score (whichever is highest) to try and answer the riddle. On a failure, it is rattled until the end of its next turn. Creatures that have an Intelligence score less than 4 or are immune to being stunned are unaffected by this trait. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per long rest.</p>",
